Data input for teal app

cdisc_dataset.Rd

Function that creates CDISC dataset object

cdisc_dataset(
  dataname,
  data,
  keys = get_cdisc_keys(dataname),
  label = data_label(data),
  code = character(0),
  vars = list()
)

Arguments

dataname

(character value)
name of dataset.
data

(data.frame)
data must contain fields defined in keys.
keys

(keys)
see keys
label

(character value)
a dataset label
code

(character value)
code to reproduce data
vars

(named list))
In case when this object code depends on the raw_data from the other RelationalDataset object(s) or other constant value, this/these object(s) should be included as named element of the list.

Please note that the order of keys is important.

Keys are not matched by name but by order. In case you want to perform:

SELECT ... FROM ADSL LEFT JOIN ADTTE on ADTTE.STUDYID = ADSL.STUDYID and ADTTE.SUBJECTUNIQUEID = ADSL.USUBJID

the keys need to be

ADSL primary: USUBJID, STUDYID

ADTTE primary: PARAMCD, foreign: SUBJECT, UNIQUEID, STUDYID, parent: ADSL

As you can see the names of foreign ADTTE are different to ADSL keys, but the order and length is equal.

Value

a dataset with connected metadata

Examples

library(random.cdisc.data)

ADSL <- radsl(cached = TRUE)

cdisc_dataset("ADSL", ADSL)
